metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #291
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash ‚Äî they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Chroma Ciphers #100
metadata.description:
A generative series using the most basic of building blocks accentuated with colors.

This is the second Ciphers generative token in a series of three.

metadata.name: Additive Synthesis #82
metadata.description:
Brushstrokes are synthesized using a large number of small lines of varying opacity, hue, and brightness. There are five styles : blocks, curves, lines, blur and partial blur; 9 color palettes, and several additional features controlling the composition of the piece.

p5.js script

metadata.name: Kink #190
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you‚Äôd like to receive a physical plot!

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Pumpkin Head #10
metadata.description: The creatures observed within the desolate cemetery of the city are commonly known as "pumpkin heads." According to local accounts, these entities are believed to be the most horrifying creatures in the entire city, instilling sheer terror in those who encounter them. It is rumored that the mere sound of their voices has the power to awaken the dormant zombies, causing them to rise from their graves once again.

metadata.name: Lonely Tree #271
metadata.description:
The bridges have been burned, wrapped in loneliness, and covered in the ashes caused by your fire.

The sound of the wind whispers, longing to carry you away.

With a shattered face, you see others in the distance, they are close, but so far away; the emptiness of this edge is closer than any of them.

But, is it? Looking within isn't hard, it's just a glance and knowing, but it's painfully hard to see.

Disjointed, you tell yourself over and over again that it wasn't for lack of effort.

But, is it? Looking within isn't hard, it's just a glance and knowing, but it's painfully hard to see.

Perhaps you weren't so lonely, perhaps you're not lonely after all.

=== 

CAUTION 

Please be aware that this artwork demands a certain level of CPU power due to the substantial number of elements that need to be rendered on the canvas. Depending on your hardware and the specific features obtained, the rendering process may take anywhere from a few seconds to several minutes to complete. 

=== 

Features

Color Scheme: 
-. Celestial Serenity
-. Serenade of Paleness
-. Tangerine Twilight
-. Verdant Sunset
-. Azure and Citrus Symphony
-. Roseate
-. Serene Whispers
-. Midnight Embers

Cliff Mode:
-. Whispering Abyss
-. Solitude's Edge
-. Eternal Overlook

Waterfall: 
-. Boolean

Signature: 
-. Boolean, if true then a position is selected: Left, Center, Right

Birds' Flock Size: 
-. 1 ("Just a Lonely Bird") to 100

Bird Color
-. Light Fill / Dark Borders
-. Dark Fill / Light Borders
-. Light Fill / Iridescent Borders
-. Dark Fill / Iridescent Borders
-. Iridescent Fill / Dark Borders
-. Crimson Fill / Iridescent Borders
-. Iridescent Fill / Crimson Borders

=== 

Controls
[s] Save image @ 2000x2600 px.
[p] Pause/Play the animation.

===

metadata.name: ecolog√≠as - A #87
metadata.description:
ecolog√≠as - A

lines are a metaphor for the communication all species engage in. We as humans have a need to leave traces - stories - that others can read and learn from. What will be the traces machines want to leave? This piece employs sinusoidal signals drawn with lines as a simple metaphor for every trace and every language, for every message and every communication.

ecolog√≠as-A is an entity that is part of a broader ecology. Released on occasion of the show "Unbound - Ecology in the Age of Machines" at Unit London. The data generated by this entity is read by a different piece minted on Ethereum, creating a link between Tezos and Ethereum, a metaphor for an ecology of blockchains.

it shares a common element with two other works released on fxhash: ecolog√≠as B and ecolog√≠as C, all of them contributing data to aforementioned pieces.

read more at https://www.iillucid.com/ecologias

15% of primary sales are donated to institutions working towards improving biodiversity and environmental efforts.

Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro
CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Built on p5.js, glsl

append &pd=N (N a number) to the URL in live view to increase/decrease resolution
press s to save current image in current resolution
press z,x,g,b,n followed by +/- to increase/decrease, respectively, brightness, contrast, gamma, blur, noise

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of Fran√ßois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.
